> see the sell. all  the lines turned down, if I had taken it on the next candle to the right that would been a prefect example of a fresh air sell

> that was the book flip

> here is a right hand edge example book and delta leading red tick

> here is another example of an aggressive sell, see the delta and book leading the red tick
> another aggressive sell see if you can spot it on the green (vertical) line

> ok here is the normal way that Ray has taught us to trade the lines, in the circle you see the book falling and the red tick is falling however deltas go up, that what we normally wanyt to see, those deltas are now trapped and we sell 
 > the agressive trade is the other way round book and delta falling with red tick left behind
> perfect orderflow sell, into a royal zone, the book and tick turned but the delta went up trapping the buyers, the delta went up on a red candle so it was a competative selling auction as well
> aggressive buy, delta and book leading tick
